{"title_page": "Kamasutra 3D", "text_new": "{{EngvarB|date=April 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2015}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Kamasutra 3D\n| image          = Kamasutra_3D_official_poster_2.jpg\n| director       = [[Rupesh Paul]]\n| producer       = venkatesh pai bolwar<br>Sagar Thacker\n| writer         = Rupesh Paul\n| music          = Saachin<br>Sreejith<br>Muhammad Ali (Background score)\n| cinematography = Sapan Narula (2D)<br />Ratheesh KG (3D)\n| editing        = [[Ajay Devlokha]]\n| starring       = [[Andria D'Souza]]<br>[[Makarand Deshpande]]\n| distributor    =\n| studio         = [[Rupesh Paul Productions Limited]]\n| country        = India\n| released       = {{Film date|2013| | |Cannes Film Festival}}\n| language       = English\n| budget         = \n| gross          =\n}}\n'''''Kamasutra 3D''''' is a 2013 Indian English-language [[3D film|3D]] [[Sex in film|erotic]] [[Drama (film and television)|drama film]] written and directed by [[Rupesh Paul]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.glamsham.com/movies/scoops/13/dec/21-news-sherlyn-chopras-kamasutra-3d-in-oscars-2014-121308.asp |title=Sherlyn Chopra's KAMASUTRA 3D n Oscars 2014 |publisher=Glamsham |date=21 December 2013 |accessdate=17 February 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/kamasutra-3d-is-not-my-film-sherlyn-chopra/story-rSXBHx4xqbPZhP57syZK5K.html |title=Kamasutra 3D is not my film: Sherlyn Chopra  |publisher=[[Hindustan Times]] |date=16 August 2016 |accessdate=19 October 2016}}</ref> The film was announced at Cannes Film Festival 2012, by Rupesh Paul- the director of the film, after the premiere of his movie, [[Saint Dracula 3D]], at the festival.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.onlookersmedia.com/rupesh-paul-going-to-direct-kamasutra-3d/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120604202326/http://www.onlookersmedia.com/rupesh-paul-going-to-direct-kamasutra-3d/ |url-status=dead |archive-date= 4 June 2012 |title=RUPESH PAUL GOING TO DIRECT KAMASUTRA 3D |accessdate=4 June 2012 }}</ref> \n\nThe first look of ''Kamasutra 3D'', was unveiled at NFDC's film bazaar on 22 November 2012 which was held on the sidelines of International Film Festival of India (IFFI) 2012 in Goa.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Bollywood/Sherlyn-Chopra-in-Kamasutra-3D-first-look-unveiled-at-Goa-film-bazaar/Article1-962835.aspx |title=Sherlyn Chopra in Kamasra 3D: first look unveiled at Goa film bazaar |publisher=Hindustan Times |date=22 November 2012 |accessdate=20 April 2013}}</ref> The ''Kamasutra 3D''&nbsp;\u2013 Photo Shoot Video with [[Sherlyn Chopra]] was revealed on 19 January 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.atbollywood.com/2013/11/Kamasutra-3D-Official-Trailer-Release-date-is-May-2014.html |title=Kamasutra 3D Official Trailer: Release dates May 2014 |publisher=Atbollywood.com |date=27 November 2013 |accessdate=10 February 2014}}</ref>i\n\n==Production==\n===Development===\n''Kamasutra 3D'' is produced under the house of [[Rupesh Paul Productions Limited]] and presented by G J Entertainments. The story has been written by the director. The film is co-produced and designed by [[Sohan Roy]], and Dr George John is the executive producer.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pardaphash.com/news/oscar-shortlisted-movie-dam999-director-kamasutra-3d-producer-sohan-roy-dr-george-john-honoured/728816.html |title=Kamasutra 3D producer Sohan Roy, Dr. George John honoured |publisher=Pardaphash.com |date= |accessdate=10 February 2014}}</ref>\n\nRupesh Paul said: {{quote|text=3D appears the best format to portray classic erotica, but it was hardly experimented till recently. It had remained as a tool to give the biggest jolt in horror movies. Nobody predicted that the Chinese stereoscopic porn would be a major hit. In fact, it out grossed 3D film Avatar. In the film, we are trying to give an extra dimension to the sexual positions described in the ancient treatise on the art of love.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.news18.com/news/india/kamasutra-3d-will-sherlyn-chopra-be-replaced-589125.html|title='Kamasutra' 3D: Will Sherlyn Chopra be replaced?|publisher=|accessdate=9 December 2017}}</ref>}} Later in June 2016 he went against this and stated: \"My film was mistaken as an erotica but it is a war film.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.asianage.com/bollywood/after-3-years-kamasutra-3d-finally-see-light-day-446 |title=After 3 years, Kamasutra 3D to finally see the light of day  author|last=Bhatnagar |first=Rohit |publisher=[[The Asian Age]] |date=25 June 2016 |accessdate=15 October 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"auto\"/>\n\n==Cast==\n{{columns-list|colwidth=22em|\n*[[Milind Gunaji]] as The Mighty King\n*King Malkhan as Warrior/Prince/Naga Sadhu\n*Tumul Balyan as Warrior/ Naga Sadhu\n*[[Makarand Deshpande]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://in.tweetwood.com/SherlynChopra/tweet/298311115681722368 |title=Sherlyn Chopra tweets: Just got to know that Makarand Deshpande has been signed for a key role in Kamasutra 3D.. |publisher=In.tweetwood.com |date= |accessdate=20 April 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130622112402/http://in.tweetwood.com/SherlynChopra/tweet/298311115681722368 |archive-date=22 June 2013 |url-status=dead }}</ref> as King\n*Maleena Kan as Princess\n*[[Sushmita Mukherjee]] as Queen \n*[[Gajendra Chauhan]] as [[Kamashastra]] [[Guru]]\n*[[Mohan Kapoor]] as Kamashastra Guru's apprentice\n*[[Amit Behl]] as Administrator\n*Kristna Saikia as Japanese Mystic Queen\n*Jay Acharya as The Warrior Prince & Kama Devi's first love (Flashback)\n*Mohit Keswani as The Mighty King (Flashback)\n*[[Andria D'Souza]] as [[Arabian]] Queen\n*Sunil Bob\n*Manoj Verma\n*Abha Paul\n*Julia Bruchhwitz\n*Hinixa Patel\n*Ziley Mawai\n* [[Dinesh Nair]]\n*Malu S Lal\n*Vishal Patni as [[Warrior]]/[[Naga Sadhu]]\n}}\n\n==Trivia==\nThe director Rupesh Paul decided to replace [[Sherlyn Chopra]], after Chopra uploaded a video clip of the photo shoot of the film on her YouTube channel without seeking his permission. He wanted to replace her with [[Eva Longoria]] or [[Mila Kunis]].<ref name=\"India Today Online - 05Feb2013 - Sherlyn Chopra out of Kamasutra 3D?\">{{cite news|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/sherlyn-chopra-out-of-kamasutra-3d/1/248986.html |title=Sherlyn Chopra out of Kamasutra 3D?|publisher=Indiatoday.intoday.in|accessdate=12 February 2014}}</ref> Chopra later apologised to him in writing, stating that she would not say or write anything about the film without the consent of the producers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/sherlyn-chopra-back-in-kamasutra-3d/article1-1017522.aspx |title=Sherlyn Chopra back in Kamasutra 3D? |publisher=Hindustan Times |date=26 February 2013 |accessdate=1 February 2014}}</ref>\n\nOn 9 February 2014, Paul filed a lawsuit against Chopra for [[defamation]], alleging that the actress had abused him on the social networking service Twitter.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2014-02-05/news-interviews/47047700_1_defamation-case-rupesh-paul-kamasutra-3d-director |title='Kamasutra 3D' director files defamation case against Sherlyn Chopra |work=[[Times of India]] |date= |accessdate=10 February 2014}}</ref> On 22 February Paul filed another complaint against Chopra, seeking [[anticipatory bail]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news-and-interviews/Rupesh-surprised-by-Sherlyns-complaint-seeks-aniticipatory-bail/articleshow/30848389.cms |title=Rupesh surprised by Sherlyn's complaint; seeks anticipatory bail |work=The Times of India |date=22 February 2014 |accessdate=1 March 2014}}</ref>\n\nBy March 2014, however, both parties dropped the lawsuits, publicly stating that they had decided to move on from the misunderstanding.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news-and-interviews/Rupesh-Paul-and-Sherlyn-Chopra-forget-differences/articleshow/31771214.cms |title=Rupesh Paul and Sherlyn Chopra forget differences |work=The Times of India |date=10 March 2014 |accessdate=1 April 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2016, Chopra after being asked about the movie after a long period of silence, told the media that she was not involved with movie. She stated that it was \"not her film\" and wished the team well.<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n\n==See also==\n*''[[Kama Sutra: A Tale of Love]]\n*''[[Tales of The Kama Sutra: The Perfumed Garden]]''\n*''[[Tales of The Kama Sutra 2: Monsoon]]''\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb title|2527238|Kamasutra 3D}}\n{{Rupesh Paul}}\n\n[[Category:2010s erotic drama films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Rupesh Paul]]\n[[Category:2010s Hindi-language films]]\n[[Category:2010s war drama films]]\n[[Category:Indian war drama films]]\n[[Category:Indian erotic drama films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:Films based on the Kama Sutra]]\n[[Category:2013 films]]\n[[Category:Indian 3D films]]\n[[Category:Films featuring an item number]]\n[[Category:Films set in ancient India]]\n[[Category:Films using computer-generated imagery]]\n[[Category:Indian epic films]]\n[[Category:Indian historical drama films]]\n[[Category:Unreleased Indian films]]\n[[Category:2013 3D films]]\n[[Category:Erotic romance films]]\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=April 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2015}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Kamasutra 3D\n| image          = Kamasutra_3D_official_poster_2.jpg\n| director       = [[Rupesh Paul]]\n| producer       = venkatesh pai bolwar<br>Sagar Thacker\n| writer         = Rupesh Paul\n| music          = Saachin<br>Sreejith<br>Muhammad Ali (Background score)\n| cinematography = Sapan Narula (2D)<br />Ratheesh KG (3D)\n| editing        = [[Ajay Devlokha]]\n| starring       = [[Andria D'Souza]]<br>[[Makarand Deshpande]]\n| distributor    =\n| studio         = [[Rupesh Paul Productions Limited]]\n| country        = India\n| released       = {{Film date|2013| | |Cannes Film Festival}}\n| language       = English\n| budget         = \n| gross          =\n}}\n'''''Kamasutra 3D''''' is a 2013 Indian English-language [[3D film|3D]] [[Sex in film|erotic]] [[Drama (film and television)|drama film]] written and directed by [[Rupesh Paul]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.glamsham.com/movies/scoops/13/dec/21-news-sherlyn-chopras-kamasutra-3d-in-oscars-2014-121308.asp |title=Sherlyn Chopra's KAMASUTRA 3D n Oscars 2014 |publisher=Glamsham |date=21 December 2013 |accessdate=17 February 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/kamasutra-3d-is-not-my-film-sherlyn-chopra/story-rSXBHx4xqbPZhP57syZK5K.html |title=Kamasutra 3D is not my film: Sherlyn Chopra  |publisher=[[Hindustan Times]] |date=16 August 2016 |accessdate=19 October 2016}}</ref> The film was announced at Cannes Film Festival 2012, by Rupesh Paul- the director of the film, after the premiere of his movie, [[Saint Dracula 3D]], at the festival.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.onlookersmedia.com/rupesh-paul-going-to-direct-kamasutra-3d/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120604202326/http://www.onlookersmedia.com/rupesh-paul-going-to-direct-kamasutra-3d/ |url-status=dead |archive-date= 4 June 2012 |title=RUPESH PAUL GOING TO DIRECT KAMASUTRA 3D |accessdate=4 June 2012 }}</ref> \n\nThe first look of ''Kamasutra 3D'', was unveiled at NFDC's film bazaar on 22 November 2012 which was held on the sidelines of International Film Festival of India (IFFI) 2012 in Goa.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Bollywood/Sherlyn-Chopra-in-Kamasutra-3D-first-look-unveiled-at-Goa-film-bazaar/Article1-962835.aspx |title=Sherlyn Chopra in Kamasra 3D: first look unveiled at Goa film bazaar |publisher=Hindustan Times |date=22 November 2012 |accessdate=20 April 2013}}</ref> The ''Kamasutra 3D''&nbsp;\u2013 Photo Shoot Video with [[Sherlyn Chopra]] was revealed on 19 January 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.atbollywood.com/2013/11/Kamasutra-3D-Official-Trailer-Release-date-is-May-2014.html |title=Kamasutra 3D Official Trailer: Release dates May 2014 |publisher=Atbollywood.com |date=27 November 2013 |accessdate=10 February 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Production==\n===Development===\n''Kamasutra 3D'' is produced under the house of [[Rupesh Paul Productions Limited]] and presented by G J Entertainments. The story has been written by the director. The film is co-produced and designed by [[Sohan Roy]], and Dr George John is the executive producer.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pardaphash.com/news/oscar-shortlisted-movie-dam999-director-kamasutra-3d-producer-sohan-roy-dr-george-john-honoured/728816.html |title=Kamasutra 3D producer Sohan Roy, Dr. George John honoured |publisher=Pardaphash.com |date= |accessdate=10 February 2014}}</ref>\n\nRupesh Paul said: {{quote|text=3D appears the best format to portray classic erotica, but it was hardly experimented till recently. It had remained as a tool to give the biggest jolt in horror movies. Nobody predicted that the Chinese stereoscopic porn would be a major hit. In fact, it out grossed 3D film Avatar. In the film, we are trying to give an extra dimension to the sexual positions described in the ancient treatise on the art of love.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.news18.com/news/india/kamasutra-3d-will-sherlyn-chopra-be-replaced-589125.html|title='Kamasutra' 3D: Will Sherlyn Chopra be replaced?|publisher=|accessdate=9 December 2017}}</ref>}} Later in June 2016 he went against this and stated: \"My film was mistaken as an erotica but it is a war film.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.asianage.com/bollywood/after-3-years-kamasutra-3d-finally-see-light-day-446 |title=After 3 years, Kamasutra 3D to finally see the light of day  author|last=Bhatnagar |first=Rohit |publisher=[[The Asian Age]] |date=25 June 2016 |accessdate=15 October 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"auto\"/>\n\n==Cast==\n{{columns-list|colwidth=22em|\n*[[Milind Gunaji]] as The Mighty King\n*King Malkhan as Warrior/Prince/Naga Sadhu\n*Tumul Balyan as Warrior/ Naga Sadhu\n*[[Makarand Deshpande]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://in.tweetwood.com/SherlynChopra/tweet/298311115681722368 |title=Sherlyn Chopra tweets: Just got to know that Makarand Deshpande has been signed for a key role in Kamasutra 3D.. |publisher=In.tweetwood.com |date= |accessdate=20 April 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130622112402/http://in.tweetwood.com/SherlynChopra/tweet/298311115681722368 |archive-date=22 June 2013 |url-status=dead }}</ref> as King\n*Maleena Kan as Princess\n*[[Sushmita Mukherjee]] as Queen \n*[[Gajendra Chauhan]] as [[Kamashastra]] [[Guru]]\n*[[Mohan Kapoor]] as Kamashastra Guru's apprentice\n*[[Amit Behl]] as Administrator\n*Kristna Saikia as Japanese Mystic Queen\n*Jay Acharya as The Warrior Prince & Kama Devi's first love (Flashback)\n*Mohit Keswani as The Mighty King (Flashback)\n*[[Andria D'Souza]] as [[Arabian]] Queen\n*Sunil Bob\n*Manoj Verma\n*Abha Paul\n*Julia Bruchhwitz\n*Hinixa Patel\n*Ziley Mawai\n* [[Dinesh Nair]]\n*Malu S Lal\n*Vishal Patni as [[Warrior]]/[[Naga Sadhu]]\n}}\n\n==Trivia==\nThe director Rupesh Paul decided to replace [[Sherlyn Chopra]], after Chopra uploaded a video clip of the photo shoot of the film on her YouTube channel without seeking his permission. He wanted to replace her with [[Eva Longoria]] or [[Mila Kunis]].<ref name=\"India Today Online - 05Feb2013 - Sherlyn Chopra out of Kamasutra 3D?\">{{cite news|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/sherlyn-chopra-out-of-kamasutra-3d/1/248986.html |title=Sherlyn Chopra out of Kamasutra 3D?|publisher=Indiatoday.intoday.in|accessdate=12 February 2014}}</ref> Chopra later apologised to him in writing, stating that she would not say or write anything about the film without the consent of the producers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/sherlyn-chopra-back-in-kamasutra-3d/article1-1017522.aspx |title=Sherlyn Chopra back in Kamasutra 3D? |publisher=Hindustan Times |date=26 February 2013 |accessdate=1 February 2014}}</ref>\n\nOn 9 February 2014, Paul filed a lawsuit against Chopra for [[defamation]], alleging that the actress had abused him on the social networking service Twitter.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2014-02-05/news-interviews/47047700_1_defamation-case-rupesh-paul-kamasutra-3d-director |title='Kamasutra 3D' director files defamation case against Sherlyn Chopra |work=[[Times of India]] |date= |accessdate=10 February 2014}}</ref> On 22 February Paul filed another complaint against Chopra, seeking [[anticipatory bail]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news-and-interviews/Rupesh-surprised-by-Sherlyns-complaint-seeks-aniticipatory-bail/articleshow/30848389.cms |title=Rupesh surprised by Sherlyn's complaint; seeks anticipatory bail |work=The Times of India |date=22 February 2014 |accessdate=1 March 2014}}</ref>\n\nBy March 2014, however, both parties dropped the lawsuits, publicly stating that they had decided to move on from the misunderstanding.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news-and-interviews/Rupesh-Paul-and-Sherlyn-Chopra-forget-differences/articleshow/31771214.cms |title=Rupesh Paul and Sherlyn Chopra forget differences |work=The Times of India |date=10 March 2014 |accessdate=1 April 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2016, Chopra after being asked about the movie after a long period of silence, told the media that she was not involved with movie. She stated that it was \"not her film\" and wished the team well.<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n\n==See also==\n*''[[Kama Sutra: A Tale of Love]]\n*''[[Tales of The Kama Sutra: The Perfumed Garden]]''\n*''[[Tales of The Kama Sutra 2: Monsoon]]''\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb title|2527238|Kamasutra 3D}}\n{{Rupesh Paul}}\n\n[[Category:2010s erotic drama films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Rupesh Paul]]\n[